<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="337" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1127,1029,1596]" pageId="4" pageNumber="337">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,268,1029,1052]" pageId="4" pageNumber="337">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male with head and scutum almost completely black, notauli reaching about 0.5 length of scutum, basivolsella with lateral medial process and not fused with paramere.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="337" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1127,1029,1596]" pageId="4" pageNumber="337">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,360,1093,1116]" pageId="4" pageNumber="337">
Description. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[297,353,1093,1116]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="337">Male</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Fully winged; length 
<quantity box="[597,682,1093,1116]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="4" pageNumber="337" unit="mm" value="2.4">2.4 mm</quantity>
. Head black, except mandible testaceous; antenna brown; mesosoma black; metasoma brown; legs brown. Antenna filiform; antennal segments in following proportions: 6: 5: 6.5: 6.5: 7: 8: 7: 7: 7: 9. Head dull, granulated; frontal line only shortly present near clypeus; occipital carina complete; POL = 7; OL = 4; OOL = 4; OPL = 4; TL = 4; greatest breadth of posterior ocelli shorter than OPL (2: 4). Scutum, scutellum and metanotum dull, granulated. Notauli incomplete, reaching about 0.5 length of scutum. Propodeum reticulate rugose. Forewing hyaline, without dark transverse bands; stigmal vein regularly curved. Basivolsella (
<figureCitation box="[698,780,1317,1340]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[151,182,1520,1539]" captionTargetBox="[242,1039,775,1496]" captionTargetId="figure-205@6.[238,1040,758,1496]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 1. A–B – male genitalia (right half removed):A – Aphelopus severancei sp. nov. (holotype); B – A. vernonensis Olmi, 2009 (holotype); C – Conganteon lymanorum sp. nov., chela (holotype). Scale bar: 0.14 mm for A and C; 0.09 mm for B." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5304735" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5304735/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="337">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
) with lateral medial process and two subdistal bristles. Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1127,1029,1596]" box="[181,390,1381,1404]" pageId="4" pageNumber="337">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[181,271,1381,1404]" pageId="4" pageNumber="337">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[181,264,1381,1404]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="337">Female</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="337" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1127,1029,1596]" pageId="4" pageNumber="337">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,402,1413,1436]" pageId="4" pageNumber="337">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
Based on the characters summarized in the above diagnosis, in the Afrotropical Region the new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Olmi, 2009" authorityName="Olmi" authorityYear="2009" box="[695,1075,1445,1468]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Aphelopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vernonensis">
<emphasis box="[695,943,1445,1468]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="337">Aphelopus vernonensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="OLMI M." box="[952,1075,1445,1468]" pageId="4" pageNumber="337" pagination="447 - 460" refId="ref30997" refString="OLMI M. 2009: New species of South African Dryinidae (Hymenoptera: Chrysidoidea). African Invertebrates 50: 447 - 460." type="journal article" year="2009">Olmi, 2009</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(see keys of 
<bibRefCitation author="OLMI M." box="[236,352,1477,1500]" pageId="4" pageNumber="337" pagination="1 - 1913" refId="ref30398" refString="OLMI M. 1984: A revision of the Dryinidae (Hymenoptera). Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute 37: 1 - 1913." type="journal article" year="1984">OLMI 1984</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="OLMI M." box="[362,420,1477,1500]" pageId="4" pageNumber="337" pagination="447 - 460" refId="ref30997" refString="OLMI M. 2009: New species of South African Dryinidae (Hymenoptera: Chrysidoidea). African Invertebrates 50: 447 - 460." type="journal article" year="2009">2009</bibRefCitation>
). The main difference regards the position of the lateral process of the basivolsella (medial in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Olmi &amp; Copeland &amp; Guglielmino &amp; Icipe" authorityYear="2015" box="[441,585,1509,1532]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Aphelopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="severancei">
<emphasis box="[441,585,1509,1532]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="337">A. severancei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[600,685,1509,1532]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[151,182,1520,1539]" captionTargetBox="[242,1039,775,1496]" captionTargetId="figure-205@6.[238,1040,758,1496]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 1. A–B – male genitalia (right half removed):A – Aphelopus severancei sp. nov. (holotype); B – A. vernonensis Olmi, 2009 (holotype); C – Conganteon lymanorum sp. nov., chela (holotype). Scale bar: 0.14 mm for A and C; 0.09 mm for B." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5304735" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5304735/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="337">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
), distal in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Olmi" authorityYear="2009" box="[799,957,1509,1532]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Aphelopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vernonensis">
<emphasis box="[799,957,1509,1532]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="337">A. vernonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[972,1054,1509,1532]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[151,182,1520,1539]" captionTargetBox="[242,1039,775,1496]" captionTargetId="figure-205@6.[238,1040,758,1496]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 1. A–B – male genitalia (right half removed):A – Aphelopus severancei sp. nov. (holotype); B – A. vernonensis Olmi, 2009 (holotype); C – Conganteon lymanorum sp. nov., chela (holotype). Scale bar: 0.14 mm for A and C; 0.09 mm for B." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5304735" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5304735/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="337">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
)). The shape of the basivolsella is the most important character used for differentiating males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dalman" authorityYear="1823" box="[151,264,1573,1596]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Aphelopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,264,1573,1596]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="337">Aphelopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="OLMI M." box="[278,407,1573,1596]" pageId="4" pageNumber="337" refId="ref30507" refString="OLMI M. 1994 a: The Dryinidae and Embolemidae (Hymenoptera: Chrysidoidea) of Fennoscandia and Denmark. Fauna Entomologica Scandinavica. Vol. 30. E. J. Brill, Leiden, 100 pp." type="book" year="1994">OLMI 1994a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="OLMI M." box="[418,486,1573,1596]" pageId="4" pageNumber="337" refId="ref30679" refString="OLMI M. 1999 a: Hymenoptera Dryinidae-Embolemidae. Fauna d'Italia. Vol. 37. Calderini Editore, Bologna, 425 pp." type="book" year="1999">1999a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="XU Z. &amp; OLMI M. &amp; HE J." box="[497,652,1573,1596]" pageId="4" pageNumber="337" pagination="1 - 460" refId="ref31752" refString="XU Z., OLMI M. &amp; HE J. 2013: Dryinidae of the Oriental region (Hymenoptera: Chrysidoidea). Zootaxa 3614: 1 - 460." type="journal article" year="2013">XU et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="OLMI M. &amp; VIRLA E. G." box="[663,877,1573,1596]" pageId="4" pageNumber="337" pagination="1 - 534" refId="ref31334" refString="OLMI M. &amp; VIRLA E. G. 2014: Dryinidae of the Neotropical region (Hymenoptera: Chrysidoidea). Zootaxa 3792: 1 - 534." type="journal article" year="2014">OLMI &amp; VIRLA 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
